// directory_ingest.proto — Recorder → Directory ingest channel.
//
// DirectoryIngest is the mirror of RecorderControl: where RecorderControl
// pushes assignments FROM Directory TO Recorder, DirectoryIngest pushes
// state, segment index, and AI events FROM Recorder TO Directory.
//
// All three RPCs are CLIENT-streaming — the recorder opens a long-lived
// stream and pushes batches of updates. The server responds with a single
// summary at close (or on periodic flush).
//
// Why client-streaming instead of unary-per-event:
//   - segment index entries can land at hundreds per minute for a busy site
//   - AI events come in bursts
//   - state updates are coalesced by camera
// One persistent stream is cheaper than thousands of HTTP requests.

